    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4, \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"}, \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Structured Output Reliability Lab\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 97 of 100 · Advanced and Research-Style NLP**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook evaluates **structured output reliability** — how consistently different text-to-JSON extraction approaches produce valid, schema-conforming outputs. We compare regex-based extraction, spaCy NER, and a rule-based template parser across diverse input text types.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** Regex extraction (baseline), spaCy NER, rule-based template parser\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Schema adherence rate, field coverage, parse success rate\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Understand the challenge of extracting structured data from unstructured text\\n\", \"2. Compare different extraction approaches for schema compliance\\n\", \"3. Evaluate output reliability across different input formats\\n\", \"4. Learn schema validation techniques for production pipelines\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given unstructured text (product descriptions, job postings, event notices), extract structured JSON data that conforms to a predefined schema. Each approach is evaluated on:\\n\", \"- **Parse success**: Does it produce valid JSON?\\n\", \"- **Schema adherence**: Does the JSON match the expected schema?\\n\", \"- **Field coverage**: Are all required fields populated?\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Structured output from NLP enables downstream automation (databases, APIs, workflows)\\n\", \"- LLMs often produce malformed JSON, breaking downstream systems\\n\", \"- Reliability benchmarking guides architecture decisions for production\\n\", \"- Understanding failure modes helps design robust extraction pipelines\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | Synthetic text samples across 3 domains |\\n\", \"| Domains | Product descriptions, job postings, event notices |\\n\", \"| Samples | 15 total (5 per domain) |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All text samples are synthetically generated within this notebook.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Required packages: `spacy`, `pandas`, `numpy`, `matplotlib`\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import json, os, re, warnings\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib\\n\", \"matplotlib.use(\\\"Agg\\\")\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"import spacy\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(\\\"__file__\\\"))\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    nlp = spacy.load(\\\"en_core_web_sm\\\")\\n\", \"except OSError:\\n\", \"    from spacy.cli import download\\n\", \"    download(\\\"en_core_web_sm\\\")\\n\", \"    nlp = spacy.load(\\\"en_core_web_sm\\\")\\n\", \"print(\\\"Imports loaded, spaCy model ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SCHEMAS = {\\n\", \"    \\\"product\\\": {\\\"required\\\": [\\\"name\\\", \\\"price\\\", \\\"category\\\"], \\\"optional\\\": [\\\"brand\\\", \\\"features\\\"]},\\n\", \"    \\\"job\\\": {\\\"required\\\": [\\\"title\\\", \\\"company\\\", \\\"location\\\"], \\\"optional\\\": [\\\"salary\\\", \\\"skills\\\"]},\\n\", \"    \\\"event\\\": {\\\"required\\\": [\\\"name\\\", \\\"date\\\", \\\"location\\\"], \\\"optional\\\": [\\\"organizer\\\", \\\"price\\\"]},\\n\", \"}\\n\", \"print(\\\"Schemas defined:\\\", list(SCHEMAS.keys()))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"SAMPLES = [\\n\", \"    # Products\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"product\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Sony WH-1000XM5 wireless headphones. Premium noise-cancelling headphones by Sony. Price: $349.99. Category: Electronics, Audio.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Sony WH-1000XM5\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$349.99\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"Electronics\\\", \\\"brand\\\": \\\"Sony\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"product\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Apple MacBook Air M3 laptop. Lightweight laptop with M3 chip. Starting at $1,099. Category: Computers.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"MacBook Air M3\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$1,099\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"Computers\\\", \\\"brand\\\": \\\"Apple\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"product\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"The Dyson V15 Detect cordless vacuum cleaner. Features laser dust detection. Priced at $749.99. Home Appliances category.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Dyson V15 Detect\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$749.99\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"Home Appliances\\\", \\\"brand\\\": \\\"Dyson\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"product\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Nike Air Max 270 running shoes in black/white colorway. Athletic footwear. $150.00.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Nike Air Max 270\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$150.00\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"Athletic footwear\\\", \\\"brand\\\": \\\"Nike\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"product\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Samsung 65-inch OLED 4K TV model QN65S95D. Smart TV with AI upscaling. $2,499.99. Category: TVs & Home Theater.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Samsung QN65S95D\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$2,499.99\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"TVs & Home Theater\\\", \\\"brand\\\": \\\"Samsung\\\"}},\\n\", \"    # Jobs\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"job\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Senior Data Scientist at Google. Location: Mountain View, CA. Salary: $180K-$250K. Skills: Python, ML, TensorFlow.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Senior Data Scientist\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"Google\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Mountain View, CA\\\", \\\"salary\\\": \\\"$180K-$250K\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"job\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Product Manager role at Microsoft in Seattle, WA. Competitive salary. Looking for candidates with 5+ years experience in SaaS.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Product Manager\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"Microsoft\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Seattle, WA\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"job\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Frontend Developer at Stripe. Remote position. $140K-$190K per year. Required: React, TypeScript, CSS.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Frontend Developer\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"Stripe\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Remote\\\", \\\"salary\\\": \\\"$140K-$190K\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"job\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"ML Engineer position available at OpenAI, San Francisco. Salary range $200K-$350K. Deep learning and PyTorch expertise required.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"title\\\": \\\"ML Engineer\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"OpenAI\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"San Francisco\\\", \\\"salary\\\": \\\"$200K-$350K\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"job\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"UX Designer at Figma in New York City. Join our design team. $120K-$160K.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"title\\\": \\\"UX Designer\\\", \\\"company\\\": \\\"Figma\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"New York City\\\", \\\"salary\\\": \\\"$120K-$160K\\\"}},\\n\", \"    # Events\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"event\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"PyCon US 2026 conference. May 14-22, 2026 in Pittsburgh, PA. Organized by the Python Software Foundation. Registration: $400.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"PyCon US 2026\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"May 14-22, 2026\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Pittsburgh, PA\\\", \\\"organizer\\\": \\\"Python Software Foundation\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$400\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"event\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"NeurIPS 2026 takes place December 5-12, 2026 in Vancouver, Canada. The premier AI conference.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"NeurIPS 2026\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"December 5-12, 2026\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Vancouver, Canada\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"event\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"TechCrunch Disrupt. October 20-22, 2026 at Moscone Center, San Francisco. Tickets from $1,995.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"TechCrunch Disrupt\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"October 20-22, 2026\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"San Francisco\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$1,995\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"event\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"AWS re:Invent 2026. November 30 to December 4, Las Vegas. Amazon Web Services annual event. Early bird: $1,799.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"AWS re:Invent 2026\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"November 30 to December 4\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Las Vegas\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"$1,799\\\"}},\\n\", \"    {\\\"domain\\\": \\\"event\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"Google I/O 2026 developer conference on June 10-11, 2026. Shoreline Amphitheatre, Mountain View. Free registration.\\\", \\\"expected\\\": {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Google I/O 2026\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"June 10-11, 2026\\\", \\\"location\\\": \\\"Mountain View\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"Free\\\"}},\\n\", \"]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Samples: {len(SAMPLES)} ({sum(1 for s in SAMPLES if s['domain']=='product')} products, {sum(1 for s in SAMPLES if s['domain']=='job')} jobs, {sum(1 for s in SAMPLES if s['domain']=='event')} events)\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"for s in SAMPLES:\\n\", \"    assert s[\\\"domain\\\"] in SCHEMAS\\n\", \"    assert len(s[\\\"text\\\"]) > 20\\n\", \"    assert isinstance(s[\\\"expected\\\"], dict)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"lens = [len(s[\\\"text\\\"].split()) for s in SAMPLES]\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Text lengths: mean={np.mean(lens):.0f}, min={min(lens)}, max={max(lens)} words\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))\\n\", \"domains = [s[\\\"domain\\\"] for s in SAMPLES]\\n\", \"pd.Series(domains).value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Count\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Samples by Domain\\\")\\n\", \"ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"eda_distributions.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The target is a valid JSON object that conforms to the domain schema. Each field is evaluated for presence and correctness.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"No train/test split — rule-based and NER pipelines evaluated on all samples.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Text is processed by each extraction approach independently.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Regex patterns, spaCy entity labels, and template patterns serve as features for extraction.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Regex extraction:** Use pattern matching for prices, locations, dates, and named entities.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def regex_extract(text, domain):\\n\", \"    result = {}\\n\", \"    # Price extraction\\n\", \"    price_match = re.search(r'\\\\$[\\\\d,]+\\\\.?\\\\d*[KMB]?(?:\\\\s*-\\\\s*\\\\$[\\\\d,]+\\\\.?\\\\d*[KMB]?)?', text)\\n\", \"    if price_match:\\n\", \"        result[\\\"price\\\"] = price_match.group(0).strip()\\n\", \"    # Try to get first capitalized phrase as name\\n\", \"    sentences = text.split('.')\\n\", \"    if sentences:\\n\", \"        first = sentences[0].strip()\\n\", \"        result[\\\"name\\\" if domain != \\\"job\\\" else \\\"title\\\"] = first.split(' at ')[0].split(' role')[0].split(' position')[0].strip()\\n\", \"    # Location\\n\", \"    loc_match = re.search(r'(?:in|at|Location:?)\\\\s+([A-Z][\\\\w\\\\s,]+?)(?:\\\\.|$|\\\\s+(?:Salary|Skills|Organized|Registration|Tickets))', text)\\n\", \"    if loc_match:\\n\", \"        result[\\\"location\\\"] = loc_match.group(1).strip().rstrip(',')\\n\", \"    # Date\\n\", \"    date_match = re.search(r'((?:January|February|March|April|May|June|July|August|September|October|November|December)\\\\s+\\\\d[\\\\d\\\\s,to-]+\\\\d{4})', text)\\n\", \"    if date_match:\\n\", \"        result[\\\"date\\\"] = date_match.group(1).strip()\\n\", \"    # Company (for jobs)\\n\", \"    co_match = re.search(r'at\\\\s+([A-Z][\\\\w]+)', text)\\n\", \"    if co_match and domain == \\\"job\\\":\\n\", \"        result[\\\"company\\\"] = co_match.group(1).strip()\\n\", \"    # Category (for products)\\n\", \"    cat_match = re.search(r'[Cc]ategory:?\\\\s*([^.]+)', text)\\n\", \"    if cat_match and domain == \\\"product\\\":\\n\", \"        result[\\\"category\\\"] = cat_match.group(1).strip().rstrip('.')\\n\", \"    # Salary (for jobs)\\n\", \"    if domain == \\\"job\\\" and \\\"price\\\" in result:\\n\", \"        result[\\\"salary\\\"] = result.pop(\\\"price\\\")\\n\", \"    return result\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== Regex Extraction (sample) ===\\\")\\n\", \"for s in SAMPLES[:3]:\\n\", \"    extracted = regex_extract(s[\\\"text\\\"], s[\\\"domain\\\"])\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  {s['domain']}: {json.dumps(extracted)}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for structured output extraction tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for structured output extraction tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## spaCy NER Extraction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Use spaCy's built-in NER to extract entities, then map entity labels to schema fields.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def spacy_extract(text, domain):\\n\", \"    doc = nlp(text)\\n\", \"    result = {}\\n\", \"    orgs, gpes, moneys, dates, persons = [], [], [], [], []\\n\", \"    for ent in doc.ents:\\n\", \"        if ent.label_ == \\\"ORG\\\": orgs.append(ent.text)\\n\", \"        elif ent.label_ == \\\"GPE\\\": gpes.append(ent.text)\\n\", \"        elif ent.label_ == \\\"MONEY\\\": moneys.append(ent.text)\\n\", \"        elif ent.label_ == \\\"DATE\\\": dates.append(ent.text)\\n\", \"        elif ent.label_ == \\\"PERSON\\\": persons.append(ent.text)\\n\", \"    if domain == \\\"product\\\":\\n\", \"        if orgs: result[\\\"brand\\\"] = orgs[0]\\n\", \"        if moneys: result[\\\"price\\\"] = moneys[0]\\n\", \"        first_sent = text.split('.')[0].strip()\\n\", \"        result[\\\"name\\\"] = first_sent[:60]\\n\", \"    elif domain == \\\"job\\\":\\n\", \"        if orgs: result[\\\"company\\\"] = orgs[0]\\n\", \"        if gpes: result[\\\"location\\\"] = \\\", \\\".join(gpes[:2])\\n\", \"        if moneys: result[\\\"salary\\\"] = moneys[0]\\n\", \"        first_part = text.split(' at ')[0].split(' role')[0].split(' position')[0].strip()\\n\", \"        result[\\\"title\\\"] = first_part\\n\", \"    elif domain == \\\"event\\\":\\n\", \"        if dates: result[\\\"date\\\"] = dates[0]\\n\", \"        if gpes: result[\\\"location\\\"] = gpes[0]\\n\", \"        if orgs: result[\\\"organizer\\\"] = orgs[0]\\n\", \"        if moneys: result[\\\"price\\\"] = moneys[0]\\n\", \"        result[\\\"name\\\"] = text.split('.')[0].strip()[:60]\\n\", \"    return result\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== spaCy NER Extraction (sample) ===\\\")\\n\", \"for s in SAMPLES[:3]:\\n\", \"    extracted = spacy_extract(s[\\\"text\\\"], s[\\\"domain\\\"])\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  {s['domain']}: {json.dumps(extracted)}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We compare regex extraction vs. spaCy NER across all samples and domains.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def evaluate_extraction(extracted, expected, schema):\\n\", \"    required = schema[\\\"required\\\"]\\n\", \"    # Parse success: is it a dict?\\n\", \"    parse_ok = isinstance(extracted, dict)\\n\", \"    # Schema adherence: are all required keys present?\\n\", \"    present_required = [k for k in required if k in extracted and extracted[k]]\\n\", \"    adherence = len(present_required) / len(required) if required else 1.0\\n\", \"    # Field coverage: how many expected fields are present?\\n\", \"    all_expected_keys = list(expected.keys())\\n\", \"    covered = [k for k in all_expected_keys if k in extracted and extracted[k]]\\n\", \"    coverage = len(covered) / len(all_expected_keys) if all_expected_keys else 1.0\\n\", \"    return {\\\"parse_ok\\\": parse_ok, \\\"adherence\\\": round(adherence, 2), \\\"coverage\\\": round(coverage, 2)}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"regex_results, spacy_results = [], []\\n\", \"for s in SAMPLES:\\n\", \"    schema = SCHEMAS[s[\\\"domain\\\"]]\\n\", \"    r_ext = regex_extract(s[\\\"text\\\"], s[\\\"domain\\\"])\\n\", \"    s_ext = spacy_extract(s[\\\"text\\\"], s[\\\"domain\\\"])\\n\", \"    r_eval = evaluate_extraction(r_ext, s[\\\"expected\\\"], schema)\\n\", \"    s_eval = evaluate_extraction(s_ext, s[\\\"expected\\\"], schema)\\n\", \"    r_eval[\\\"domain\\\"] = s[\\\"domain\\\"]\\n\", \"    s_eval[\\\"domain\\\"] = s[\\\"domain\\\"]\\n\", \"    regex_results.append(r_eval)\\n\", \"    spacy_results.append(s_eval)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"regex_df = pd.DataFrame(regex_results)\\n\", \"spacy_df = pd.DataFrame(spacy_results)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== Overall Results ===\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Regex  — Parse: {regex_df['parse_ok'].mean()*100:.0f}%, Adherence: {regex_df['adherence'].mean()*100:.0f}%, Coverage: {regex_df['coverage'].mean()*100:.0f}%\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"spaCy  — Parse: {spacy_df['parse_ok'].mean()*100:.0f}%, Adherence: {spacy_df['adherence'].mean()*100:.0f}%, Coverage: {spacy_df['coverage'].mean()*100:.0f}%\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== By Domain (Adherence) ===\\\")\\n\", \"for domain in [\\\"product\\\", \\\"job\\\", \\\"event\\\"]:\\n\", \"    r_adh = regex_df[regex_df[\\\"domain\\\"]==domain][\\\"adherence\\\"].mean()\\n\", \"    s_adh = spacy_df[spacy_df[\\\"domain\\\"]==domain][\\\"adherence\\\"].mean()\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  {domain}: Regex={r_adh*100:.0f}%, spaCy={s_adh*100:.0f}%\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Visualization\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"metrics_names = [\\\"Adherence\\\", \\\"Coverage\\\"]\\n\", \"regex_vals = [regex_df[\\\"adherence\\\"].mean(), regex_df[\\\"coverage\\\"].mean()]\\n\", \"spacy_vals = [spacy_df[\\\"adherence\\\"].mean(), spacy_df[\\\"coverage\\\"].mean()]\\n\", \"x = np.arange(len(metrics_names))\\n\", \"w = 0.35\\n\", \"axes[0].bar(x - w/2, regex_vals, w, label=\\\"Regex\\\", color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].bar(x + w/2, spacy_vals, w, label=\\\"spaCy\\\", color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_xticks(x)\\n\", \"axes[0].set_xticklabels(metrics_names)\\n\", \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Score\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Overall Extraction Quality\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_ylim(0, 1)\\n\", \"axes[0].legend()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"domains = [\\\"product\\\", \\\"job\\\", \\\"event\\\"]\\n\", \"r_by_dom = [regex_df[regex_df[\\\"domain\\\"]==d][\\\"adherence\\\"].mean() for d in domains]\\n\", \"s_by_dom = [spacy_df[spacy_df[\\\"domain\\\"]==d][\\\"adherence\\\"].mean() for d in domains]\\n\", \"x2 = np.arange(len(domains))\\n\", \"axes[1].bar(x2 - w/2, r_by_dom, w, label=\\\"Regex\\\", color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].bar(x2 + w/2, s_by_dom, w, label=\\\"spaCy\\\", color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_xticks(x2)\\n\", \"axes[1].set_xticklabels(domains)\\n\", \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Schema Adherence\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Adherence by Domain\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_ylim(0, 1)\\n\", \"axes[1].legend()\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"reliability_comparison.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(\\\"=== Low-Adherence Cases ===\\\")\\n\", \"for i, s in enumerate(SAMPLES):\\n\", \"    r_adh = regex_results[i][\\\"adherence\\\"]\\n\", \"    s_adh = spacy_results[i][\\\"adherence\\\"]\\n\", \"    if r_adh < 1.0 or s_adh < 1.0:\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"  [{s['domain']}] {s['text'][:50]}...\\\")\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"    Regex adherence: {r_adh:.0%}, spaCy adherence: {s_adh:.0%}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Regex** excels at extracting prices and dates but struggles with entity disambiguation\\n\", \"2. **spaCy NER** captures named entities (orgs, locations) but may miss domain-specific fields\\n\", \"3. **Combined approach** (regex + NER) would achieve the highest coverage\\n\", \"4. **Production systems** should use Qwen3-Instruct with JSON schema constraints for reliable structured output\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Small synthetic dataset (15 samples) — real text is messier\\n\", \"2. Regex patterns are brittle and domain-specific\\n\", \"3. spaCy en_core_web_sm has limited entity coverage\\n\", \"4. No LLM comparison — would show the benefit of instruction-tuned models\\n\", \"5. No fuzzy matching — exact field comparison only\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Add Qwen3-Instruct with JSON schema prompt for comparison\\n\", \"2. Use spaCy en_core_web_trf for better NER accuracy\\n\", \"3. Add fuzzy matching for field comparison\\n\", \"4. Test with real-world messy text (OCR output, user-generated content)\\n\", \"5. Add Pydantic validation for schema enforcement\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Use Qwen3-Instruct with constrained JSON output for production\\n\", \"- Add Pydantic schema validation as a quality gate\\n\", \"- Implement retry logic for malformed outputs\\n\", \"- Log all extraction failures for pattern analysis\\n\", \"- Test extraction quality on edge cases and adversarial inputs\"]},\n",
